           </li>
           
           <li class="courseListItem" style="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;padding:0 0 10px;list-style-image:none;list-style-type:none;">
           









  
    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/physics/PCS/106.html" title="PCS 106 - Physics for the Health Sciences" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">PCS 106</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Physics for the Health Sciences</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">An introduction to the physical ideas related to the fields of environmental and occupational health; mechanics, work/energy, fluids, sound, thermodynamics, basic electricity, the electromagnetic spectrum and nuclear quantities.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. Lab: 0.5 hrs. Tutorial: 0.5 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListWeight"><span class="courseInfoLabels">GPA weight: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">1.00</span></div>
	
	
