    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/physics/PCS/228.html" title="PCS 228 - Electricity and Magnetism" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">PCS 228</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Electricity and Magnetism</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">Fundamentals of Classical Electromagnetism. Electrostatics: charges, electrostatic force, electric field, electric flux, Gauss's law, electric potential, electrostatic energy, properties of conductors. Magnetostatics: Magnetic field, magnetic flux, electric current and Ampere's Law. Faraday's Law of electromagnetic induction. Maxwell equations: electromagnetic waves and the nature of light.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. Lab: 1.5 hrs. Tutorial: 1 hr. </span></div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListWeight"><span class="courseInfoLabels">GPA weight: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">1.00</span></div>
	
	
